Hi Jason-

Fair point. I am selecting things that seem to me to be pretty different,
and so I would expect most of the time they would be in different species
and be preserved...but if they are in the same species I agree they
shouldn&#39;t be preserved.

Assuming they are in different species, is there another switch that needs
to be thrown to preserve them or should they be preserved with my settings?

Also, am I right that I need to turn crossover off (by setting
MutateOnlyProbability to 1), or does your code know not to cross elites?

Maybe I could go with another tack: Is there a way to increase the number of
organisms that elitism protects unmutated? (e.g. the top N most fit in the
pop)?




